Stand-up comedian Kenny Blaq has said Nigerian comedians will certainly perform exceptionally in of the world’s most coveted entertainment hubs, O2 arena in London. The ‘music-median’ in a chat with Hip TV insisted Nigerian comic acts can ‘sell out’ the O2 arena with the right plug. According to him, Nigerian comedians have the wherewithal in terms of great content to actualise that feat. “By God’s grace, we are going to sell out the O2 one day. Yes, Nigerian comedians can actually sell out the O2. We’ve got the content, we just need the right plug. “By God’s grace, you never can tell. Tomorrow, it might just be ‘Kenny Blaq life at the O2’ shutting it down.   ‘Portable needs rehab not shows’     American actor William Hurt dies at 71     My daughter loves Shola Ogudu- Mercy Johnson   “So, Nigerian comedians can actually shut down the O2 like Wizkid, Davido and Burna. So, watch out!” He added: “Keep supporting the industry. It’s going to happen very very soon. You never can tell, if might even be tomorrow. So, watch out.” The award-winning comic star started his comedy career in 2008, and has performed at top comedy events within and outside Nigeria Blaq’s first internationally headlined event was staged at the Indigo O2 on September 30, 2018, titled “Kenny Blaq ‘State of Mind'”, in partnership with SMADE a UK based international show promoter Also in 2018, he was recognised as one of the 100 most influential youths in Africa.